nodes.bodyText:
The tops variable seems to store qualifier parameter hierarchies for the enclosing class of the local variable, rather than on the type of the local variable itself. So in
ClassWithQualParam1 {
    void m() {
        ClassWithQualParam2 local;
    }
}
We would need to apply the defaults to local regardless of the qualifier parameters on ClassWithQualParam1. I think this means moving it might be incorrect, because the enclosing class might not have a qualifier parameter at all and we would still apply the new defaults.

